# 1. 無意識のうちに

Mizuki: <...>
Mizuki: <I guess Yuki isn't coming today either...>
Kanade: <It seems that way...>
Kanade: <However, she's been sending us her lyrics, and we've been able to meet her at the diner on occasion...>
Kanade: <But it's been two weeks now since she last worked with us on Nightcord...>
Ena: <Do you think her mom's still spying on her...?>
Kanade: <I have to think so...>
Mizuki: (Two weeks...)
Mizuki: (It's already been that long since then...)
Kanade: Mafuyu's mom and I parted ways once we exited the hotel...
Mizuki: Geez...
Mizuki: No room in her life for music. How can she say that...?
Ena: Seriously, what's wrong with her...?
Ena: She's just completely ignoring how Mafuyu actually feels...!
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (I got a bad feeling when I overheard Mafuyu speak with her on voice chat that one time...)
Mizuki: (But Kanade's story confirmed my suspicions. Mafuyu's mom... She...)
Mizuki: (She doesn't care at all how Mafuyu feels...)
Ena: Um, Kanade...?
Ena: Are you sure you don't want to tell Mafuyu about this...?
Ena: Once she knows how her mom really thinks, she might...
Kanade: I've already gone over that in my head. Unfortunately...
Kanade: Even if we were to tell Mafuyu, I'm not sure she'd be able to process this information... At least, not right now...
Ena: What...?
Kanade: When KAITO arrived...
KAITO: She's doing everything she can to destroy who you really are. How can you even think about showing her any mercy?
Mafuyu: Destroy who I am...?
Mafuyu: No...
Mafuyu: She cares about me. She's not trying to...
KAITO: Oh, come on. Open your eyes.
KAITO: You know exactly what she's trying to do. But you just keep—
Mafuyu: No... No...! Mom... She...!
Kanade: I have a feeling that Mafuyu continues to believe that her mother genuinely cares about her, and would never do anything to cause her pain...
Kanade: She's still clinging to that somehow...
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: I got that feeling too...
Mizuki: And I think she's doing it subconsciously...
Kanade: I agree...
Kanade: So, even if we did tell her what her mother said, there's a high likelihood that she wouldn't immediately accept it...
Kanade: If anything, it could just make things worse and cause her more pain...
Ena: Yeah, I get that! But...!
Ena: I mean, what are we supposed to do...?
Kanade: I understand how you feel, but we simply don't have a solution right now.
Kanade: But I'm confident that there is a way out there to help her.
Kanade: So, let's try to figure that out.
Ena: Right...
Ena: Sitting back and watching while Mafuyu suffers just doesn't seem right.
Mizuki: Yeah!
Mizuki: Let's brainstorm and see what we can do!
Mizuki: (We spent a lot of time thinking after that, but...)
Mizuki: <Hey, wanna meet in SEKAI for a bit...?>
Ena: <What? Now?>
Mizuki: <For, you know...? A little change of scenery! Seriously, my shoulders are starting to ache after sitting in this chair for so long...>
Mizuki: <Also, I wanna tell Miku and the others about Yuki's current situation!>
Kanade: <Yes, I agree with you on that...>
Kanade: <Then, let's take a quick break in SEKAI.>
Mizuki: <Woohoo!>
Mizuki: <Meet you there in five! And bring snacks!>
